# ============================================================
# HISTORY CORE RUNTIME
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: runtime
domain: history
scope: history.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines core runtime handling for history.

## runtime_scope
Runtime covers historical reference visibility,
sequence-aware display,
reconstruction display,
restricted-history handling,
and safe failure rendering.

## current_view_state
Runtime-visible history state must distinguish:
- retained historical record
- reconstructed historical view
- restricted historical view
- archived historical view

## validation_rules
- historical basis must resolve
- reference mode must resolve
- reconstruction scope must be valid
- disclosure scope must be valid

## failure_modes
- invalid historical basis
- invalid reconstruction scope
- invalid reference mode
- safe runtime fallback

## observability
Runtime must emit enough signals
to distinguish retained history,
reconstructed history,
restricted history,
and failure surface.

## review_checklist
- historical runtime is explicit
- reconstruction-aware display is explicit
- failure handling is explicit
